s to human knowledge, and that can also be measured against governmental standards, rules and regulations. The contributors present a radical and much-needed intervention that will interest all academics engaged with creative practice research. It also contains one of Thomas Elsaesser’s final pieces of writing, a unique personal account of the making of his first and only film The Sun Island.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion picturesxStudy and teaching (Higher). 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Research.2bisacsh1 aAlabi-Hundeyin, Tunde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtakav, Eylem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuckland, Warren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClancy, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaniels, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEadie, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsaesser, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFong, Rosa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMassoumi, Nariman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMock, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiotrowska, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRifeser, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStarkier, Isabelle, econtri